# dnsutils
# A set of DNS client utilities, such as `dig`, `nslookup`.

# Query A record for a domain:
dig example.com

# Query a specific DNS server:
dig @8.8.8.8 example.com

# Query MX records for a domain:
dig example.com MX

# Lookup a domain using nslookup:
nslookup example.com

# Query the reverse DNS (PTR record) for an IP address:
dig -x 8.8.8.8
